# Generate a list of normally distributed random numbers
    rand_list = stats.norm.rvs(size=size)

    # Create a histogram of the random numbers
    plt.hist(rand_list, bins=50, density=True, alpha=0.6)

    # Calculate the probability density function (PDF) using the KDE method
    kde = stats.gaussian_kde(rand_list)
    x = np.linspace(-6, 6, 1000)  # Set the range of x values for the PDF
    pdf = kde.evaluate(x)  # Calculate the PDF values for each x value

    # Plot the PDF
    plt.plot(x, pdf, color='red', linewidth=3)
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Histogram with PDF')

    return plt.gcf()  # Return the current figure object

# Generate a list of normally distributed random numbers
    random_num = np.random.normal(0, 1, size)

    # Create a figure and axis object
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    # Plot the histogram of the random numbers
    ax.hist(random_num, bins=20, density=True, edgecolor='black')

    # Plot the probability density function (PDF) of the normal distribution
    x = np.linspace(min(random_num), max(random_num), 1000)
    pdf = stats.norm.pdf(x, np.mean(random_num), np.std(random_num))
    ax.plot(x, pdf, 'r-', linewidth=2)

    # Set axis labels and title
    ax.set_xlabel('Value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('Histogram and PDF of Normally Distributed Random Numbers')

    return fig
